(73, 1, '2015-06-15 19:16:24', '2015-06-15 19:16:24', '<p class="txt-normal"><img title="" src="http://www.isvindia.org/work/research/images/Research.png" alt="" align="left" border="0" /><span class="b1">Interserve India</span> conducted survey research among Middle Class Indians of other Faiths. The aim was to develop contextually appropriate approaches of sharing the Good News among middle class Indians. The primary information used in this survey was on socio-religious perspectives of other faiths concerning their knowledge, attitudes and practices; to develop possible ways of making Christ known to them personally. This survey was undertaken among selected major cities of India. They are: Ahmedabad, Bangalore, Chennai, Delhi, Guwahati, Hyderabad, Kolkata, Mumbai, Nagpur and Pune.</p>\r\n<p class="txt-normal">For more information on this study contact: contactingisv@gmail.com</p>', 'Research', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'research', '', '', '2015-06-15 19:16:24', '2015-06-15 19:16:24', '', 50, 'http://local.wordpress.dev/?page_id=73', 5, 'page', '', 0),
